<h2>3. Technical Architecture</h2>

<h3>Frontend (Client)</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Framework</strong>: React 18 (Vite)</li>
<li><strong>Language</strong>: TypeScript</li>
<li><strong>UI Library</strong>: Material UI (MUI v5)</li>
<li><strong>State Management</strong>: React Hooks</li>
<li><strong>Routing</strong>: React Router DOM v6</li>
<li><strong>Data Fetching</strong>: Axios</li>
</ul>

<h3>Backend (Server)</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>Framework</strong>: .NET 8 ASP.NET Core Web API</li>
<li><strong>Language</strong>: C#</li>
<li><strong>Data Access</strong>: Dapper (High-performance micro-ORM)</li>
<li><strong>Database</strong>: Microsoft SQL Server</li>
<li><strong>API Documentation</strong>: Swagger / OpenAPI</li>
</ul>

<h2>4. Database Setup</h2>
<p>All necessary SQL scripts are located in the <code>database/</code> folder.</p>
<ul>
<li><code>01_Schema_Create.sql</code>: Base tables (Users, Customers, etc.)</li>
<li><code>05_Charges_Schema.sql</code>: <strong>[NEW]</strong> Schema for Charges Configuration.</li>
<li><code>07_Collections_Table.sql</code>: Schema for Doc Collections.</li>
<li><code>08_GL_Table.sql</code>: Schema for General Ledger.</li>
</ul>

